U.S. House of Representatives Speaker Nancy Pelosi is expected to stopover in Taiwan after repeated warnings from China to stay away. In the face of Washington's repeated attempts to challenge China on the core issue defining bilateral relations, China is still trying to be the voice of reason. In this episode of BizBeat, CGTN's Michael Wang argues Pelosi's attempt to play the Taiwan card against China jeopardizes regional peace and gambles with global peace and security.